          <div property="content:encoded" class="field-item even"><p><strong>Part 2:</strong> I spoke with the <a href="http://topshelfmodules.com/">Top Shelf Modules</a> team – <a href="http://topshelfmodules.com/users/susan-rust">Susan Rust</a>, <a href="http://topshelfmodules.com/users/ryan-cross">Ryan Cross</a>, <a href="http://topshelfmodules.com/users/rik-de-boer">Rik de Boer</a>, and <a href="http://topshelfmodules.com/users/karl-scheirer">Karl Scheirer</a> – on November 4, 2013. In part two, we go into more depth about TSM's mission and discuss the sustainability (or otherwise) of Drupal's volunteer-based development model and the various efforts and experiments underway to change, improve, or "fix" it, some more pragmatic – like TSM and <a href="http://drupalfund.us">drupalfund.us</a>, some more idealistic, like <a href="https://www.gittip.com/alexpott/">Gittip sponsorships</a> and similar.</p>
